  36:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****     [..]
  37:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      As prerequisite, fill in the HAL_XSPI_MspInit() :
  38:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) Enable XSPI clocks interface with __HAL_RCC_XSPI_CLK_ENABLE().
  39:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) Reset XSPI Peripheral with __HAL_RCC_XSPI_FORCE_RESET() and __HAL_RCC_XSPI_RELEASE_RESET()
  40:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) Enable the clocks for the XSPI GPIOS with __HAL_RCC_GPIOx_CLK_ENABLE().
  41:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) Configure these XSPI pins in alternate mode using HAL_GPIO_Init().
  42:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) If interrupt or DMA mode is used, enable and configure XSPI global
  43:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****          interrupt with HAL_NVIC_SetPriority() and HAL_NVIC_EnableIRQ().
  44:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) If DMA mode is used, enable the clocks for the XSPI DMA channel
  45:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****          with __HAL_RCC_DMAx_CLK_ENABLE(), configure DMA with HAL_DMA_Init(),
  46:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****          link it with XSPI handle using __HAL_LINKDMA(), enable and configure
  47:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****          DMA channel global interrupt with HAL_NVIC_SetPriority() and HAL_NVIC_EnableIRQ().
  48:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****     [..]
  49:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      Configure the fifo threshold, the memory mode, the memory type, the
  50:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      device size, the CS high time, the free running clock, the clock mode,
  51:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      the wrap size, the clock prescaler, the sample shifting, the hold delay
  52:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      and the CS boundary using the HAL_XSPI_Init() function.
  53:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****     [..]
  54:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      When using Hyperbus, configure the RW recovery time, the access time,
  55:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      the write latency and the latency mode using the HAL_XSPI_HyperbusCfg()
  56:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      function.
  57:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c **** 
  58:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****     *** Indirect functional mode ***
  59:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****     ================================
  60:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****     [..]
  61:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      In regular mode, configure the command sequence using the HAL_XSPI_Command()
  62:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      or HAL_XSPI_Command_IT() functions :
  63:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) Instruction phase : the mode used and if present the size, the instruction
  64:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****          opcode and the DTR mode.
  65:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) Address phase : the mode used and if present the size, the address
  66:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****          value and the DTR mode.
  67:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) Alternate-bytes phase : the mode used and if present the size, the
  68:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****          alternate bytes values and the DTR mode.
  69:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) Dummy-cycles phase : the number of dummy cycles (mode used is same as data phase).
  70:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) Data phase : the mode used and if present the number of bytes and the DTR mode.
  71:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) Data strobe (DQS) mode : the activation (or not) of this mode
  72:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) IO selection : to access external memory.
  73:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) Operation type : always common configuration.
  74:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****     [..]
  75:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      In Hyperbus mode, configure the command sequence using the HAL_XSPI_HyperbusCmd()
  76:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      function :
  77:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) Address space : indicate if the access will be done in register or memory
  78:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) Address size
  79:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) Number of data
  80:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) Data strobe (DQS) mode : the activation (or not) of this mode
  81:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****     [..]
  82:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      If no data is required for the command (only for regular mode, not for
ARM GAS  /tmp/ccRyvVSM.s 			page 3


  83:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      Hyperbus mode), it is sent directly to the memory :
  84:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) In polling mode, the output of the function is done when the transfer is complete.
  85:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) In interrupt mode, HAL_XSPI_CmdCpltCallback() will be called when the transfer is complete
  86:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****     [..]
  87:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      For the indirect write mode, use HAL_XSPI_Transmit(), HAL_XSPI_Transmit_DMA() or
  88:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      HAL_XSPI_Transmit_IT() after the command configuration :
  89:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) In polling mode, the output of the function is done when the transfer is complete.
  90:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) In interrupt mode, HAL_XSPI_FifoThresholdCallback() will be called when the fifo threshold
  91:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****          is reached and HAL_XSPI_TxCpltCallback() will be called when the transfer is complete.
  92:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) In DMA mode, HAL_XSPI_TxHalfCpltCallback() will be called at the half transfer and
  93:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****          HAL_XSPI_TxCpltCallback() will be called when the transfer is complete.
  94:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****     [..]
  95:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      For the indirect read mode, use HAL_XSPI_Receive(), HAL_XSPI_Receive_DMA() or
  96:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      HAL_XSPI_Receive_IT() after the command configuration :
  97:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) In polling mode, the output of the function is done when the transfer is complete.
  98:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) In interrupt mode, HAL_XSPI_FifoThresholdCallback() will be called when the fifo threshold
  99:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****          is reached and HAL_XSPI_RxCpltCallback() will be called when the transfer is complete.
 100:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) In DMA mode, HAL_XSPI_RxHalfCpltCallback() will be called at the half transfer and
 101:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****          HAL_XSPI_RxCpltCallback() will be called when the transfer is complete.
