 107:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****     [..]
 108:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      Configure the auto-polling functional mode using the HAL_XSPI_AutoPolling()
 109:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      or HAL_XSPI_AutoPolling_IT() functions :
 110:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) The size of the status bytes, the match value, the mask used, the match mode (OR/AND),
 111:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****          the polling interval and the automatic stop activation.
 112:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****     [..]
 113:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      After the configuration :
 114:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) In polling mode, the output of the function is done when the status match is reached. The
 115:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****          automatic stop is activated to avoid an infinite loop.
 116:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) In interrupt mode, HAL_XSPI_StatusMatchCallback() will be called each time the status matc
 117:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c **** 
 118:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****     *** Memory-mapped functional mode ***
 119:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****     =====================================
 120:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****     [..]
 121:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      Configure the command sequence by the same way than the indirect mode except
 122:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      for the operation type in regular mode :
 123:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) Operation type equals to read configuration : the command configuration
 124:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****          applies to read access in memory-mapped mode
 125:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) Operation type equals to write configuration : the command configuration
 126:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****          applies to write access in memory-mapped mode
 127:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) Both read and write configuration should be performed before activating
 128:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****          memory-mapped mode
 129:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****     [..]
 130:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      Configure the memory-mapped functional mode using the HAL_XSPI_MemoryMapped()
 131:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      functions :
 132:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      (+) The timeout activation and the timeout period.
 133:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****     [..]
 134:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      After the configuration, the XSPI will be used as soon as an access on the AHB is done on
 135:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      the address range. HAL_XSPI_TimeOutCallback() will be called when the timeout expires.
 136:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c ****      HAL_XSPI_IsMemoryMapped() can be used to verify whether memory-mapped mode is configured or no
 137:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_xspi.c **** 
